meta {
  name: Agent Claim Confirm (auth.md POST /agent/identity/claim/confirm)
  type: http
  seq: 101
}

post {
  url: {{baseUrl}}/agent/identity/claim/confirm
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{accessJwt}}
}

body:json {
  {
    "user_code": "{{userCode}}"
  }
}

vars:pre-request {
  baseUrl: http://localhost:8080
}

docs {
  # POST /agent/identity/claim/confirm

  The human-in-the-loop gate of the auth.md claim ceremony (spec Step 4). The account owner —
  authenticated with either a **wallet session token** (the opaque `sessions`-table token Obsign
  holds; what the claim-approval screen sends) or a **full-access** OAuth/XRPC access token
  (app-password and agent-derived tokens are refused) — submits the `user_code` the agent showed
  them. Same dual-credential owner guard as the `/v1/agents` surface.

  On success the server binds the registration to the caller's DID (for an ownerless `anonymous`
  identity — a registration already bound at registration time may be confirmed only by that owner),
  mints the post-claim `identity_assertion`, and flips the identity `active → claimed` so its
  assertion can be exchanged at `POST /oauth/token` (jwt-bearer grant).

  ## Response (200)

  ```json
  {
    "registration_id": "reg_...",
    "status": "claimed",
    "did": "did:plc:..."
  }
  ```

  ## Errors

  - 401 invalid_token: missing/invalid credential, or a token below full access (e.g. an app password)
  - 403 access_denied: agent-derived token, a revoked identity, or a code bound to another account
  - 400 invalid_request: missing `user_code`, or `registration_id` doesn't match the code
  - 400 invalid_user_code: unknown code
  - 400 claim_expired: the user code has expired
  - 400 claimed_or_in_flight: the code/registration has already been claimed
}
